# UI Copy Style

## Trailing Periods

Remove trailing periods from all UI chrome text. Keep them only in body content.

**UI chrome (no period):**
- Labels: `YouTube URL`, `Tone`, `Section Density`
- Buttons: `Generate`, `Copy`, `EN / 中文`
- Headings / titles: `YouTube Caption → AI workspace`
- Taglines / subtitles: `Paste a URL. Stream a live summary…` ← exception: mid-copy sentence breaks are fine, but the **final** label string has no trailing period
- Status / toast messages: `Ready`, `Generating summary…`, `Error fetching transcript`
- Placeholder text: `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=…`
- Tab labels, pill labels, section headers, tooltips

**Body content (keep periods):**
- Transcript cue text
- AI-generated prose in summary, mindmap, people, related-videos panels
- Detail pane paragraphs

## Quick Rule

> If a user reads it as a **label or control**, drop the period.  
> If a user reads it as a **sentence in a document**, keep the period.
